{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845668975,"sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","part":{"id":"prt_d78a66ee30016VbX70Mi49yIRO","messageID":"msg_d78a6639b001lr22tCODC9t0x7","sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-004\n2: title: WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n3: module: pkg/workloadmanager\n4: language: Go\n5: size: M\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n9: # Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n10: # Language: Go\n11: # Size: M\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: service-framework\n21:   description: |\n22:     Build the HTTP service framework for WorkloadManager, providing RESTful APIs\n23:     for workload lifecycle management including create, query, update, and delete\n24:     operations. The framework should support middleware, routing, error handling,\n25:     and standardized response formats.\n26: \n27: # Scope\n28: scope:\n29:   in:\n30:     - pkg/workloadmanager/server package structure\n31:     - HTTP router and handler setup\n32:     - RESTful API endpoints for workload management\n33:     - Middleware (logging, error recovery, request validation)\n34:     - Response formatting and error handling\n35:     - Configuration loading for server settings\n36:   out:\n37:     - Business logic implementation (separate AR)\n38:     - Authentication/Authorization (separate AR)\n39:     - Database persistence layer (separate AR)\n40:     - Metrics and monitoring (separate AR)\n41: \n42: # Acceptance Criteria\n43: acceptance:\n44:   - HTTP server starts and listens on configured port\n45:   - Router correctly routes requests to handlers\n46:   - Middleware chain executes for all requests\n47:   - Standardized JSON response format\n48:   - Proper error handling with HTTP status codes\n49:   - Graceful shutdown support\n50:   - Configuration-driven server settings\n51: \n52: # References\n53: references:\n54:   - https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n55:   - https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin (or chosen framework)\n56:   - AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime types\n57:   - AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter types\n58:   - AR-003: CRD Shared Types\n59: \n60: # Estimation\n61: estimation:\n62:   size: M\n63:   story_points: 5\n64:   days: 3\n\n(End of file - total 64 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-004\ntitle: WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\nmodule: pkg/workloadmanager\nlanguage: Go\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n# Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n# Language: Go\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: service-framework","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775845668941,"end":1775845668973}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845668979,"sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","part":{"id":"prt_d78a6739d001TULJIa4SaYkLhm","messageID":"msg_d78a6639b001lr22tCODC9t0x7","sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Phase 1: Project Structure Setup\n4: \n5: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/` directory structure\n6: - [ ] Create subpackages: `server/`, `handlers/`, `middleware/`, `config/`\n7: - [ ] Define interface contracts between layers\n8: \n9: ## Phase 2: HTTP Server Foundation\n10: \n11: - [ ] Implement base server structure with configurable options\n12: - [ ] Setup HTTP router (choose framework: Gin/Chi/std lib)\n13: - [ ] Implement server lifecycle (start, stop, graceful shutdown)\n14: - [ ] Add health check endpoint\n15: \n16: ## Phase 3: Middleware Implementation\n17: \n18: - [ ] Request logging middleware\n19: - [ ] Error recovery/panic handling middleware\n20: - [ ] Request ID generation middleware\n21: - [ ] CORS middleware (if needed)\n22: - [ ] Request timeout middleware\n23: \n24: ## Phase 4: API Endpoints & Handlers\n25: \n26: - [ ] Define RESTful routes for workload operations:\n27:   - POST /api/v1/workloads - Create workload\n28:   - GET /api/v1/workloads - List workloads\n29:   - GET /api/v1/workloads/:id - Get workload details\n30:   - PUT /api/v1/workloads/:id - Update workload\n31:   - DELETE /api/v1/workloads/:id - Delete workload\n32: - [ ] Implement handler stubs (business logic to be filled in later AR)\n33: \n34: ## Phase 5: Response & Error Handling\n35: \n36: - [ ] Define standardized JSON response structure\n37: - [ ] Implement error response formatter\n38: - [ ] Map internal errors to HTTP status codes\n39: - [ ] Add validation error handling\n40: \n41: ## Phase 6: Configuration\n42: \n43: - [ ] Define server configuration schema\n44: - [ ] Implement configuration loading from file/env\n45: - [ ] Support for port, timeout, and middleware settings\n46: \n47: ## Phase 7: Testing & Validation\n48: \n49: - [ ] Unit tests for middleware\n50: - [ ] Unit tests for handlers\n51: - [ ] Integration tests for server startup\n52: - [ ] Verify graceful shutdown behavior\n53: \n54: ## Checklist\n55: \n56: - [ ] Code follows Go best practices\n57: - [ ] All exported functions have documentation\n58: - [ ] Error handling is consistent\n59: - [ ] Configuration is externalized\n60: - [ ] Tests cover happy path and error cases\n61: - [ ] No business logic in framework layer\n\n(End of file - total 61 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Project Structure Setup\n\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/` directory structure\n- [ ] Create subpackages: `server/`, `handlers/`, `middleware/`, `config/`\n- [ ] Define interface contracts between layers\n\n## Phase 2: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n- [ ] Implement base server structure with configurable options\n- [ ] Setup HTTP router (choose framework: Gin/Chi/std lib)\n- [ ] Implement server lifecycle (start, stop, graceful shutdown)\n- [ ] Add health check endpoint\n\n## Phase 3: Middleware Implementation\n\n- [ ] Request logging middleware\n- [ ] Error recovery/panic handling middleware\n- [ ] Request ID generation middleware","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/plan.md","time":{"start":1775845668944,"end":1775845668976}}}}
