for all fields using camelCase naming\n33: - [ ] Add struct documentation comments\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Task 3: Define Error Types and HTTP Error Mapping\n38: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/errors/errors.go` exists with HTTPError type\n39: \n40: - [ ] Create `errors.go` file in `pkg/workloadmanager/errors/`\n41: - [ ] Define `HTTPError` struct with Code, Message, StatusCode, Details, RequestID fields\n42: - [ ] Implement `Error()` method for HTTPError\n43: - [ ] Add JSON tags using camelCase naming\n44: - [ ] Define error constructor functions: NewNotFoundError, NewValidationError\n45: - [ ] Define error constructor functions: NewConflictError, NewInternalError, NewTimeoutError\n46: - [ ] Add service error constants: ErrWorkloadNotFound, ErrWorkloadAlreadyExists\n47: - [ ] Add service error constants: ErrValidationFailed\n48: - [ ] Add error mapping function `MapServiceError()` with switch statement\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## Task 4: Define Request and Response DTOs\n53: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/types/` contains request.go and response.go\n54: \n55: - [ ] Create `request.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/`\n56: - [ ] Define `WorkloadType` string type with constants: WorkloadTypeAgentRuntime, WorkloadTypeCodeInterpreter\n57: - [ ] Define `CreateWorkloadRequest` struct with Namespace, Name, Type, AgentRuntimeSpec, CodeInterpreterSpec, Labels, Annotations fields\n58: - [ ] Define `UpdateWorkloadRequest` struct with AgentRuntimeSpec, CodeInterpreterSpec, Labels, Annotations fields\n59: - [ ] Define `ListWorkloadsRequest` struct with Namespace, Type, LabelSelector, FieldSelector, Limit, Continue fields\n60: - [ ] Add validation tags using `validate:` struct tags\n61: - [ ] Create `response.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/`\n62: - [ ] Define `Response` struct with Success, Data, Error, RequestID, Timestamp fields\n63: - [ ] Define `ErrorDetail` struct with Code, Message, Details fields\n64: - [ ] Define `WorkloadResponse` struct with Type, Namespace, Name, UID, CreatedAt, ResourceVersion, Labels, Annotations, Spec, Status fields\n65: - [ ] Define `ListWorkloadsResponse` struct with Items, Total, Continue, RemainingItemCount fields\n66: - [ ] Define `HealthResponse` struct with Status, Checks, Version fields\n67: - [ ] Define `HealthCheck` struct with Status, Message, LastChecked fields\n68: - [ ] Define `WorkloadEvent` struct with Type, Workload fields\n69: - [ ] Add JSON tags using camelCase naming for all DTOs\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## Task 5: Define Service Interface\n74: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/service/service.go` exists with WorkloadService interface\n75: \n76: - [ ] Create `service.go` file in `pkg/workloadmanager/service/`\n77: - [ ] Define `WorkloadService` interface with CreateWorkload method\n78: - [ ] Add GetWorkload, ListWorkloads, UpdateWorkload, DeleteWorkload methods\n79: - [ ] Add WatchWorkloads method to interface\n80: - [ ] Define `WatchOptions` struct with Namespace, Type, LabelSelector, ResourceVersion fields\n81: - [ ] Define `WatchStream` interface with Next() and Stop() methods\n82: - [ ] Add package-level interface documentation\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Task 6: Implement RequestID Middleware\n87: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/server/middleware/requestid.go` exists and generates UUIDs\n88: \n89: - [ ] Create `requestid.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/server/middleware/`\n90: - [ ] Define `RequestIDHeader` constant with value \"X-Request-ID\"\n91: - [ ] Implement `RequestIDMiddleware()` function returning Middleware type\n92: - [ ] Generate UUID v4 for requests without existing request ID\n93: - [ ] Propagate existing request ID from header if present\n94: - [ ] Store request ID in request context using context.WithValue\n95: - [ ] Add `GetRequestID(r *http.Request)` helper function\n96: - [ ] Write unit tests in `requestid_test.go`\n97: - [ ] Verify test: generates UUID when no header present\n98: - [ ] Verify test: propagates exi