ve >= 80% test coverage\n- [ ] Service layer has >= 80% test coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests verify end-to-end flow\n- [ ] Code follows Go naming conventions\n- [ ] Compatible with AR-004 HTTP framework\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775845931439,"end":1775845931466}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845931469,"sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","part":{"id":"prt_d78a9c3440015faSer7E86Mclp","messageID":"msg_d78a6a559001Ze5H7BL1tCp4Vu","sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/tests.md","content":"# AR-005 Tests: Sandbox Creation Handler\n\n## Test Categories\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Handler Tests\n\n| Test Case | Description | Expected Result |\n|-----------|-------------|-----------------|\n| CreateSandbox_Success | Valid creation request | 201 Created, returns SandboxResponse |\n| CreateSandbox_InvalidJSON | Malformed JSON body | 400 Bad Request |\n| CreateSandbox_ValidationError | Missing required fields | 422 Unprocessable Entity |\n| CreateSandbox_QuotaExceeded | Resources over quota | 403 Forbidden |\n| CreateSandbox_ServiceError | Internal service error | 500 Internal Server Error |\n| GetSandbox_Success | Existing sandbox ID | 200 OK, returns SandboxResponse |\n| GetSandbox_NotFound | Non-existent sandbox | 404 Not Found |\n| GetSandbox_InvalidID | Invalid ID format | 400 Bad Request |\n| ListSandboxes_Success | List all sandboxes | 200 OK, returns list |\n| ListSandboxes_WithFilters | Filter by status | 200 OK, filtered list |\n| ListSandboxes_InvalidLimit | Limit > 1000 | 400 Bad Request |\n| DeleteSandbox_Success | Existing sandbox | 200 OK |\n| DeleteSandbox_NotFound | Non-existent sandbox | 404 Not Found |\n\n#### Service Tests\n\n| Test Case | Description | Expected Result |\n|-----------|-------------|-----------------|\n| CreateSandbox_Success | Valid request | Returns SandboxResponse, status \"creating\" |\n| CreateSandbox_QuotaCheck | Exceeds quota | Returns quota exceeded error |\n| CreateSandbox_GenerateID | No ID provided | Generates UUID |\n| GetSandbox_Success | Existing ID | Returns SandboxResponse |\n| GetSandbox_NotFound | Non-existent ID | Returns not found error |\n| ListSandboxes_All | No filters | Returns all sandboxes |\n| ListSandboxes_ByStatus | Filter by status | Returns filtered results |\n| ListSandboxes_Pagination | With limit/continue | Returns paginated results |\n| DeleteSandbox_Success | Existing sandbox | Removes sandbox, returns nil |\n| DeleteSandbox_NotFound | Non-existent | Returns not found error |\n| UpdateStatus_ValidTransition | Valid status change | Updates status |\n| UpdateStatus_InvalidTransition | Invalid change | Returns error |\n| CheckQuota_WithinLimits | Valid resources | Returns nil |\n| CheckQuota_Exceeded | Over limits | Returns quota exceeded error |\n\n#### Quota Manager Tests\n\n| Test Case | Description | Expected Result |\n|-----------|-------------|-----------------|\n| CheckQuota_CPUWithinLimit | CPU under max | Allowed |\n| CheckQuota_CPUExceeded | CPU over max | Quota exceeded |\n| CheckQuota_MemoryWithinLimit | Memory under max | Allowed |\n| CheckQuota_MemoryExceeded | Memory over max | Quota exceeded |\n| CheckQuota_StorageWithinLimit | Storage under max | Allowed |\n| CheckQuota_StorageExceeded | Storage over max | Quota exceeded |\n\n#### Status Tracker Tests\n\n| Test Case | Description | Expected Result |\n|-----------|-------------|-----------------|\n| GetStatus_Exists | Existing sandbox | Returns current status |\n| GetStatus_NotExists | New sandbox | Returns \"pending\" |\n| UpdateStatus_Valid | Valid transition | Updates and returns nil |\n| UpdateStatus_Invalid | Invalid transition | Returns error |\n| StatusTransitions_PendingToCreating | Normal flow | Allowed |\n| StatusTransitions_CreatingToRunning | Normal flow | Allowed |\n| StatusTransitions_RunningToTerminating | Delete flow | Allowed |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Scenario | Description | Steps | Expected Result |\n|----------|-------------|-------|-----------------|\n| E2E_CreateSandbox | Full create flow | POST /sandboxes → Service → Response | 201 Created, sandbox persisted |\n| E2E_CreateWithQuota | Create with quota enforcement | Request exceeding quota → Response | 403 Forbidden, no sandbox created |\n| E2E_CreateAndGet | Create then retrieve | POST → GET /sandboxes/:id | Both succeed, data matches |\n| E2E_CreateAndList | Create then list | POST → GET /sandboxes | Created sandbox in list |\n| E2E_CreateAndDelete | Create then delete | POST → DELETE → GET | Delete succeeds, GET returns 404 |\n| E2E_StatusProgression | Track status changes | Create → Check status transitions | Status progresses correctly |\n\n### Load Tests\n\n| Test Case | Description | Configuration | Expected Result |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|-----------------|\n| ConcurrentCreates | Multiple parallel creations | 100 concurrent requests | All succeed, no race conditions |\n| ListPerformance | Large dataset listing | 10000 sandboxes, limit=100 | Response time < 100ms |\n| QuotaStress | Near quota limit operations | 99/100 sandboxes created | Last creation rejected correctly |\n\n### Test Data\n\n#### Valid Create Request\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"test-sandbox\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"image\": \"agentcube/sandbox:latest\",\n  \"resources\": {\n    \"cpu\": \"1\",\n    \"memory\": \"2Gi\",\n    \"storage\": \"5Gi\"\n  },\n  \"labels\": {\n    \"app\": \"test\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### Quota Exceeded Request\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"big-sandbox\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"image\": \"agentcube/sandbox:latest\",\n  \"resources\": {\n    \"cpu\": \"10\",\n    \"memory\": \"20Gi\",\n    \"storage\": \"100Gi\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### Invalid Requests\n```json\n// Missing required image\n{\n  \"name\": \"test-sandbox\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\"\n}\n\n// Invalid resource format\n{\n  \"name\": \"test-sandbox\",\n  \"image\": \"agentcube/sandbox:latest\",\n  \"resources\": {\n    \"cpu\": \"invalid\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Coverage Requirements\n\n| Component | Minimum Coverage |\n|-----------|------------------|\n| handler/ | 90% |\n| service/ | 85% |\n| types/ | 80% |\n| config/ | 80% |\n| Overall | 85% |\n\n### Test Commands\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/... -v\n\n# Run with coverage\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/... -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out\n\n# Run specific package\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/service/... -v\n\n# Run integration tests only\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/test/... -v -tags=integration\n\n# Generate coverage report\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/tests.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/tests.md","time":{"start":1775845931443,"end":1775845931468}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845931471,"sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","part":{"id":"prt_d78aa4f5e001F2bZ56UgvAzpYI","messageID":"msg_d78a6a559001Ze5H7BL1tCp4Vu","sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/notes.md","content":"# AR-005 Notes: Sandbox Creation Handler\n\n## Development Notes\n\n### Dependencies on AR-004\n\nThis AR depends on the HTTP Service Framework from AR-004:\n- Uses the router from `pkg/workloadmanager/server/router.go`\n- Follows the same handler/service/type pattern\n- Uses the same error handling and response formatting\n- Should integrate with the existing middleware chain\n\n### Design Decisions\n\n1. **In-Memory Storage**: For this initial implementation, sandbox state is stored in-memory. Future ARs may add persistent storage.\n\n2. **Synchronous Creation**: Sandbox creation is synchronous in the API response. The actual provisioning may be asynchronous internally.\n\n3. **UUID Generation**: Using UUID v4 for sandbox IDs to ensure uniqueness across restarts and distributed deployments.\n\n4. **Resource Parsing**: Using Kubernetes-style resource quantities (e.g., \"500m\", \"2Gi\") for consistency with the broader ecosystem.\n\n### Open Questions\n\n1. **Persistence**: Should we persist sandbox state to etcd/database, or keep it in-memory only?\n\n2. **Sandbox Runtime**: What is the actual runtime for sandboxes? Kubernetes pods? Containers? VMs?\n\n3. **Cleanup Policy**: Should terminated sandboxes be automatically cleaned up after a TTL?\n\n4. **Multi-tenancy**: How should tenant isolation be implemented? Kubernetes namespaces or custom isolation?\n\n5. **Metrics**: What metrics should be exposed for sandboxes? (creation time, active count, resource usage)\n\n### Implementation Notes\n\n- Start with the types and interfaces to establish contracts\n- Build the service layer with quota and status management\n- Implement handlers following AR-004 patterns\n- Write tests early to validate the design\n\n### References\n\n- AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n- Kubernetes Resource Quotas: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/policy/resource-quotas/\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/notes.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/notes.md","time":{"start":1775845931447,"end":1775845931470}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845931847,"sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","part":{"id":"prt_d78a6b88f0012Z9qLJSE1ZSqtG","messageID":"msg_d78a6a559001Ze5H7BL1tCp4Vu","sessionID":"ses_28759b764ffeCwvNXdIDS0gJeo","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/spec.yaml","content":"id: AR-005\ntitle: Sandbox 创建处理器\nmodule: pkg/workloadmanager\nlanguage: Go\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-005: Sandbox Creation Handler\n# Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n# Language: Go\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: sandbox-handler\n  description: |\n    Implement the Sandbox creation handler for the WorkloadManager that processes\n    sandbox creation requests, provisions isolated execution environments for agents,\n    and manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources. The handler should integrate with\n    the existing HTTP service framework and provide secure, isolated sandbox instances.\n\n# Scope\nscope:\n  in:\n    - Sandbox creation request handling\n    - Sandbox resource provisioning\n    - Isolation environment setup\n    - Sandbox lifecycle management (create, query, delete)\n    - Resource quota enforcement\n    - Integration with WorkloadManager service layer\n    - Sandbox status tracking and reporting\n  out:\n    - Sandbox image management (separate AR)\n    - Network policy configuration (separate AR)\n    - Storage volume management (separate AR)\n    - Advanced security policies (separate AR)\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\nacceptance:\n  - Sandbox creation request is processed and validated\n  - Sandbox resources are provisioned with proper isolation\n  - Resource quotas are enforced during creation\n  - Sandbox status is tracked and queryable\n  - Sandbox can be deleted and resources cleaned up\n  - Integration with existing WorkloadManager HTTP framework\n  - Proper error handling and status codes\n  - Unit tests achieve >= 80% coverage\n\n# References\nreferences:\n  - AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n  - AR-003: client-go Generated Code\n  - AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter Types\n  - AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime Types\n\n# Estimation\nestimation:\n  size: M\n  story_points: 5\n  days: 3\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/spec.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/spec.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775845931423,"end":1775845931844}}}}
